<br>
I suspect that this technology is going to be very unreliable and hard to get at first, and possibly will always be that way. A small power network in your house is one thing, going across the power grid is another. For one thing, the voltage at your house is just a couple hundred volts. At the transformer in your neighborhood, it jumps to a few thousand volts. When it traverses a high-voltage transmission line, the voltage is ramped up to tens of thousands of volts. Trying to modulate a recognizable signal at extremely high voltage is very difficult. Plus, transformers are mechanical devices that don't operate in a very consistant manner. They won't preserve an electronic signal as it passes through the coils. I'm not sure how they intend to overcome that, but it sounds very error-prone to me.<br>
<br>
Moreover, even in highly industrialized nations ike the U.S., power grids are notoriously &quot;dirty&quot;. The voltage often drifts all over the place -- I repeatedly see it hop from 93V to 135V here at my office -- and the power alternation is rarely a nice predictable sine wave. In other words, there's a whole lot of random noise out there that the data transmission equipment is going to have to &quot;shout&quot; over.<br>
<br>
On top of all that, house and building wiring is rarely done 100% correctly. Stuff doesn't get grounded properly, polarities get reversed by electricians, etc. Power systems vary widely from one country to another, which makes this technology expensive to expand. For example, the U.S. uses 2-phase AC. Several European countries use a 3-phase system which is entirely different and incompatible (although probably a superior design).<br>
<br>
In short, I'll believe it's theoretically possible, but from a practical standpoint, I'll believe it when I see it. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm9.showPrevMessage?topicID=2322.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm9.showNextMessage?topicID=2322.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2322.topic&index=14><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/classic/addReply.jpg border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"><a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm9.threadControl?topicID=2322.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands</a><br> <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm9.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=2322.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/subscribe.gif width=20 height=20 border=0 alt="Click to receive email notification of replies"> Click to receive email notification of replies</a> <br>  <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm9.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=2322.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/unsubscribe.gif width=20 height=20 border=0 alt="Click to stop receiving email notification of replies"> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies</a> <br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub94.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="firionaviefrm1">Firiona Vie General Chat<option value="firio